register.description: Peripheral Identification Register This register is a constant register that contains the ID and ID revision number for that module. The stores version information used to identify the module.

bitfield.description: Used to distinguish between old scheme and current.
Indicating a software compatible module family.
Indicates a Special Version for a particular device.

register.description: Global Control Register Not supported. This register contains global control to PSC.

bitfield.description: Force bit. Fer PSC 2.0, this bit is considered only if all of the conditions are true

register.description: Global Status Register This register shows the PSC global status.
Interrupt Evaluation Register This register has no storage. Read from this register returns 0.
Module Error Pending Register 0 This register records pending error conditions for all modules. Each bit represents one module.
Module Error Pending Register 1 This register records pending error conditions for all modules. Each bit represents one module.
Module Error Clear Register 0 This register has no storage. Read from this register returns 0.
Module Error Clear Register 1 This register has no storage. Read from this register returns 0.
Power Error Pending Register This register records pending error conditions for each power domain. Each bit represents one domain.
Power Error Clear Register This register has no storage. Read from this register returns 0.
External Power Control Pending Register This register records pending external power control conditions. Each bit represents one domain.

bitfield.description: External Power Control Intervention Request for Power Domain n

register.description: External Power Control Clear Register This register has no storage. Read from this register returns 0.
Power Rail Status Register This register is a read-only and shows the current rail requestor whose request is being granted and the current value of the counter associated with this requestor.

bitfield.description: Indicates Current Rail Requestor being processed by GPSC.
Indicates the current rail counter value.

register.description: Power Rail Counter Control Register This register is user programmable. It holds the counter values for rail counter. User can select one of the two counter values to be used for each power domain (see RAILSEL register). This counter is clocked by gpsc_clk.
Power Rail Counter Select Register User can use this register to select the counter value(RAILCTL) for each power domain.

bitfield.description: Rail Counter Select for Power Domain n

register.description: Power Transition Command Register This is a pseudo-command register with no actual storage. Reads return 0. One bit for each power domain.
Power Domain Transition Status Register This is a status register (read only).

bitfield.description: Power Domain n Transition Command Status
